titleInfo.title: Schultz v. Union Pacific Railroad Company
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER that the plaintiff's unopposed motion for continuance of trial and to amend the progression schedule, filing 32, is granted and, a. A jury trial of this case is set to commence, at the court's call, January 30, 2006 in Omaha, Nebraska, before the undersigned Magistrate Judge. Unless otherwise ordered, jury selection shall be at the commencement of trial. b. The Final Pretrial Conference with the undersigned magistrate judge is set for January 19, 2006 at 11:30 a.m. in the chambers of the Special Proceedings Courtroom, Roman L. HruskaUnited States Courthouse, Omaha, Nebraska. c. The deposition deadline is continued to December 23, 2005, and other deadlines which use the deposition deadline as a point of reference are extended accordingly. d. All other provisions of the court's order setting this case for trial shall remain in effect. Signed by Magistrate Judge David L. Piester on 8/22/2005. (CS, )

titleInfo.title: Schultz v. Union Pacific Railroad Company
titleInfo.subTitle: ORDER - Within thirty days of the date of this order the parties shall file a joint stipulation for dismissal (or other dispositive stipulation) with the clerk of the court and provide a draft order to the undersigned magistrate judge which will fully dispose of the case. Absent compliance with this order, this case (including all counterclaims and the like) may be dismissed without furthernotice. This case has been removed from the trial docket upon representation by the parties that the case has settled. Signed by Magistrate Judge David L. Piester on 12/16/2005. (GJG, )
